\subsection{Covariates (Universal / Residual Kriging)}{

When covariates are included in the formula (e.g., \code{y ~ x1 + x2}), the
model performs \strong{Universal Kriging} — fitting a linear trend model with
spatial correlation of residuals. Use \code{y ~ 1} for \strong{Ordinary Kriging}
(no covariates, constant mean).
}

\subsection{Spatiotemporal Kriging}{

Spatiotemporal Gaussian process modelling is supported through the \code{"gstat"},
\code{"GPvecchia"}, and \code{"PrestoGP"} engines by passing \code{time_col} as an engine
argument via \code{set_engine()}. The column specified must contain date/time
values (or numeric time indices).
}
}
\examples{
if (requireNamespace("spacetime", quietly = TRUE) &&
    requireNamespace("gstat", quietly = TRUE)) {
  data("air", package = "spacetime")

  # Convert legacy ST components from `air` to a single-day `sf` table.
  day_id <- which.max(colSums(!is.na(air)))
  air_day <- data.frame(
    station = rownames(air),
    pm10 = air[, day_id],
    day = dates[day_id],
    sp::coordinates(stations)
  )
  air_day <- air_day[stats::complete.cases(air_day$pm10), ]
  air_sf <- sf::st_as_sf(
    air_day,
    coords = c("coords.x1", "coords.x2"),
    crs = 4326,
    remove = FALSE
  )

  n_train <- floor(0.8 * nrow(air_sf))
  train_sf <- air_sf[seq_len(n_train), ]
  test_sf <- air_sf[seq.int(n_train + 1L, nrow(air_sf)), ]

  gp_spec <- gaussian_process_spatial(
    covariance_function = "exponential"
  ) |>
    parsnip::set_engine("gstat")

  gp_fit <- parsnip::fit(
    gp_spec,
    pm10 ~ coords.x1 + coords.x2,
    data = train_sf
  )

  predict(gp_fit, new_data = test_sf, type = "pred_int")
}
}
